[node name="HelpDialog" type="AcceptDialog" parent="UI"]
title = "How to Play Scoundrel"
size = Vector2i(480, 420)
dialog_text = "GOAL: Survive the dungeon. Start with 20 HP.

DECK: 44 cards (standard 52 minus red face cards & red aces).

EACH ROOM: 4 cards are dealt face-up. You MUST take at least 3.
Click a card to take it. After 3 cards, 'Next Room' appears — the
remaining card carries into the next room. You may take all 4.

MONSTERS (Clubs & Spades):
  2-10 = face value damage, J=11, Q=12, K=13, A=14.
  With a weapon: damage = monster - weapon (minimum 0).
  Weapon degrades: next use must be vs. a WEAKER monster.

WEAPONS (Diamonds, 2-10 only):
  Click to equip. Replaces your current weapon.
  Old weapon is discarded. Weapon value = card rank.

POTIONS (Hearts, 2-10 only):
  Restore HP equal to rank, capped at 20.
  Only ONE potion heals per room (extras are discarded).

RUN: Skip an entire room — monsters shuffle back into the deck,
  potions and weapons sink to the bottom. Cannot run two rooms in a row.

DEATH: Reach 0 HP.
WIN: Clear the deck."
